Show HN: Search for movies using natural language
text:
Hello HN

VXAI is an an experiment to find out how useful are text embeddings for finding movies by naturallanguage. TMDB api is used to display additional information.

The site has two search modes. In the first, you can describe the movie plot and get result. In second, based on exact movie name it will provide recommendations for other similar movies.

Looking forward to feedback!

Ask HN: What are some of the best libraries out there for scraping reviews?
text:
I'm looking to create a tool to pull in all our company reviews/comments in one place so we can respond to them... save us the time of cycling through a bunch of websites and knowing what we last read. I know I can google and I have - but I don't want to miss something that everyone is using to do this :) Thanks!

P.S. I'm language agnostic on this... I'll build a service out in whatever I need to.

Ask HN: Is there a “jump back” feature in browsers after doing Ctrl-F?
text:
When I’m browsing a long page, if I do a Ctrl-F, it will jump me to some random part in the page, and I don’t know how to get back to where I was

I would like a back button within a page, to go back to my previous location before the “jump”

As I think about it, vim has a notion of this, it’s called the jump list, and you can traverse it [1]

Does such a thing exist? I have the same issue in Mac Preview PDF viewer as well

I’m mostly using Chrome btw

[1] https://medium.com/@kadek/understanding-vims-jump-list-7e1bfc72cdf0
